<constraint_G cog:lid='ever_G' cog:link='/theorist/ethics/normative_ethic/#G'>
    Always the waycast relates the personal to the endmost goal of the person
    <requirement cog:lid='endmost_goal_recording'>
        The waycast records one’s endmost goal
        </requirement>
    <requirement cog:lid='goalward_recording'>
        The waycast records personal expressions that relate to one’s endmost goal and so define one’s way
        </requirement>
    <requirement>
        The waycast records personal expressions that relate to one’s way and so define its context
        </requirement>
    <requirement>
        The waycast traces and tracks one’s way and its context
        <cog:including>
            <r>
                The waycast traces and tracks all the world’s expressions that define one’s way and its context
                </r>
            </cog:including>
        <!--- - - - -                                                                   HERE DOWN CUSTOM
        = fix these clumsy conjunctions of 'way' and 'context'
            - here 'context' means the formalized environment of way (variants)
              that informs changes to the way definition
            | instead express their combination as a single word
                | 'variations'
                    - both
                        - temporal variations
                            - changes to one's own way
                        - spatial variations
                            - variant ways
                            - alternatives on offer
                | [something] = inner [something] + outer [something]
                    | 'definition' = inner definition + outer definition
                        < definition = inner definition + outer definition
                        - con: fails to capture the notion of the outer as a resource for inner changes
            - - - -                                                                   HERE UP CUSTOM -->
        <r>
            The definitions of a way and its context can extend across multiple wayrepos
            <r cog:link='#available'/>
            </r>
        <r>
            The extension,
            <html:a href='http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/lex/collate'>tracing</html:a> and
            <html:a href='http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/lex/track'>tracking</html:a>
            of a way and its context happen in the background of awareness
              <!-- from http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/lex/background -->
            <fact>A way context can be too big for one alone to monitor and maintain</fact>
            <fact>A way         can be too big for one alone to monitor and maintain</fact>
            <r cog:link='../#backgrounding'/>
            </r>
        </requirement>
    </constraint_G>



<constraint_F cog:lid='ever_F' cog:link='/theorist/ethics/normative_ethic/#F'>
    Always the waycast promotes a maximum, universal sum of personal freedom
    <requirement>
        The waycast is personal property, to shape and fill according to one’s will
        </requirement>
    <requirement cog:lid='available'>
        A waycast of one’s own is available to anyone who wants it
        <r cog:lid='public'>
            The waycast is a public facility
            <r cog:link='../#public_reading'/>
            </r>
        <r cog:lid='propagating'>The waycast propagates by free copying</r>
        </requirement>
    <requirement>
        The waycast is inalienable from the person
        </requirement>
    <belief>
        Personal freedom increases when useful tools are in the hands of the person
        </belief>
    </constraint_F>



